Exactly.  Each renewable producing unit that comes online shrinks the amount of CO2 calculated as being sequestered for all producers at the margin, making a GreenCoins more competitive to produce. This figure is updated and set by the GreenCoin Foundation based on a variety of widely published government and scientific reports.  To further the electric power production as an example, the current global emissions to produce 1 kWh averages to 527 grams of CO2, however, as more green power comes on line (and hopefully due to GreenCoins existence!), this global average will begin to decrease substantially. If, at some point in the future, the global average were only 250 grams CO2 per kWh and you had a system generating power at 200 grams CO2 per kWh, you are receiving only 50 grams CO2 per kWh generated which you then gets rewarded GreenCoins (this would be less than before when you were generating green power versus the 527 grams CO2 per kWh global average). This incentivizes producers to reduce their CO2 impact as much as possible to receive the most GreenCoins and continue to find ways to do so as the global problem begins to resolve.<br/></p></div>
 
